annotation.TEXT: In this level, it's possible to get 40 coins, but you gotta know where they all are!
Are all these fancy moves really necessary?
Still not all that hard.
Let's see how many coins I can get in this place!
Now let's get 40 at the goal to wrap this level up!
SMW challenge from sonshadsil94: Start a new game, and finish it in one go. Get at least 40 coins in each level when possible, and at get at least 40 stars from each goal tape.
Okay, I'm done being greedy. Coins collected in this level: 94.
You probably know that Rip Van Fishes try to flee from you while you're invincible, but have you ever noticed that sleeping ones slowly float upwards during star power?
And now for the Bowser battle. I don't have to worry about avoiding hitting anything anymore now, so it's just the run-of-the-mill fight here.
Yeah, I'm not going to need the side area. I've already hit the quota!
And here we are at Bowser's castle. I'll pick routes that have harmable enemies just to make it more challenging.
BGM: Final Fantasy IV - Victory
Watch it, Ninji! I'm trying not to kill you here!
I need 40 coins by the end of the level, so double gulping berries will certainly help. I think it's not totally necessary, though.
Or we could get 50! That works, too! Hahaha! Coins collected in this level: 56.
That's every coin in this castle, and it turns out there were exactly 40! How interesting!
BGM: Katamari Damacy - Nananan Katamari Sepia
Come on, Yoshi! Eat up!
How did I manage to squeeze between the pipe and the edge of the screen there?
BGM: Yoshi's Island - Crystal Cave
Awesome! And since I won't be encountering any more goal tapes, this is the only time I have to get a perfect here! (Also, I won't need to worry about bonus stars anymore, either!)
BGM: Super Mario Land - Muda
Coins collected in this level: 193.
The 1-up isn't needed, but why not get it anyway?
BGM: Cave Story - On to Grasstown
Man, that Castlevania music isn't getting much of a chance here!
BGM: Startropics - Sub-C
There you go!
I already have all the coins I need, so I just gotta concentrate on getting at least 40 stars.
I guess I'll do some fancy flying around with the cape to make it more interesting...
Hi, Yoshi!
Barf!
BGM: Super Bonk - Blue Sky
Barf!
Toasty! Yeah, that was bound to happen eventually.
BGM: Super Mario Kart - Rainbow Road
Ahem... I was trying to enter the door on my belly!
BGM: Castlevania: Aria of Sorrow - Castle Corridor
Uh, oh. Missed the P-switch glitch. Now I gotta hurry!
I think it's possible to get enough speed to fly here, but I don't want to waste too much time. Bye, Yoshi!
Good! Coins collected in this level: 50.
And thus, the princess is saved again! But... for how long?
Down here, collect a few, but not too many of the coins before hitting the P-switch.
Umm... For some reason, I forgot to speed up this part, so if this cutscene bores you, just jump about 20 seconds forward to skip it.
Barf!
Whoa! I've never landed quite like that before!
Okay, now to make my Yoshi grow!
It's easier to hit the panels while not riding Yoshi, because sometimes with Yoshi, you'll pass through a panel without hitting it.
Why am I bothering with this Yoshi coin? I've already hit the quota. Answer: Because I want to!
I don't need to, but I'm going underground anyway.
Still made it with time to spare.
Actually, looking back, I could've let the P-switch expire then collected a few coins from the end of the line, but obviously I achieved 40 anyway if you're watching this now!
BGM: Sonic & Knuckles - Lava Reef Zone Act 1
BGM: Kirby Super Star - Marx Battle
I can avoid most of the traffic by swimming up here.
I'm going to skip the flower, since I don't want to risk accidentally burning something later.
Whoa! That would've been bad if I pounded the ground there!
Of course, now there's a new problem. How do I get Yoshi out of here?
Screw you, flower!
Dodging this Mechakoopa is probably the trickiest part of this room.
The way the parakoopas appear here if I'm rushing through leaves a perfect gap to jump through!
And just like that, I've hit my coin quota for this level!
Getting at least 40 coins should be no problem in this level, because of those lines near the star. If I need to, I can go for the multi-coin block and berries in the side area, too.
Just moving at a moderate pace, and letting the Chucks jump over you is probably the best strategy here.
Nuts. Missed two coins. Well, it's not like I need them.
Getting 40 coins here will be a piece of cake, once I get a feather.
Note: There's no way to get 40 coins in any of the remaining levels without frying stuff or using glitches, so now this is just going to be simply a pacifist run until I reach Bowser.
Bye, Iggy!
BGM: Mega Man 2 - Boss Battle
Of course, the problem is... How do I get a feather without hurting something?
Well, the solution to my problem is in here!
There's no power up or Yoshi restrictions fortunately. Just be careful not to smack (or snack on) something that I'm not supposed to!
Coins collected in this level: Some number that's greater than 39.
BGM: Tetris GB - Type A
BGM: Super Mario Galaxy - Fire Mario
Hi, Yoshi!
BGM: Yoshi's Cookie - Battle Theme C
BGM: Super Marisa World - World 5 Theme
Oops! Missed one that I intended to collect. I hope I can still reach 40! (Since I started this level with 50, that means I need 90 by the end.)
BGM: Cave Story - Balrog's Theme
Guess I'll want to do some ballooning. Just watch out for the parakoopas.
BGM: Mega Man X - Storm Eagle's Stage
Oof! Silly mistake. However, now I don't have to worry about accidentally getting a flower here!
Now I need a bonus game perfect...
Barf!
Yes! That's 40 exactly! Now I just need 40 from the goal...
Barf!
Now I could block clone for Yoshi wings and get coins that way here, but then I'd have to make an extra trip through the level for the secret exit, so I'm not going to bother.
Actually, I want to begin the next level without Yoshi. Bye, Yoshi!
Nice! Coins collected in this level: 40, which I just said a few seconds ago!
Grabbing the star is actually a bad idea, since I'm trying NOT to hurt stuff!
Careful. Don't accidentally whack Rip Van Fish with a ? block!
Getting 40 coins in this level shouldn't be too hard.
Whenever I enter the bonus game, I must get a perfect. Lastly, no harming any enemies except for bosses, and whatever the bosses throw at me. So I'll just be gently setting this shell back down here.
Barf!
Coins collected in this level: 61.
Caution - Mole crossing!
BGM: Kirby's Adventure - Vegetable Valley
Now this level's coin total is interesting. Note that I'm starting with 46, and I'm going to go for every coin that I'm aware of.
BGM: Marble Madness - Practice Race
